The paper focuses on analyzing the activation patterns of RNNs from a linguistic point of view, specifically in the context of predicting visual scenes corresponding to input sentences and predicting the next word in the same sentence. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper explores the types of linguistic structure that RNNs learn, which could also fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses visual input, which could potentially place it in the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
